---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import SiteFooter from '../components/SiteFooter.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy · Fractune"
  description="Learn how Fractune, the architectural fluency analysis tool, processes and protects your personal data."
>
  <SiteHeader />

  <main class="page">
    <div class="page-inner">
      <h1>Privacy Policy for Fractune</h1>
      <p class="caption">Last updated: May 2026</p>

      <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
      <p>
        This privacy policy describes how Fractune (developed by Colours by
        Barslund, Denmark) processes your personal data when you use our app or
        website, contribute facade readings to the public dataset, or contact
        us for support.
      </p>
      <address>
        Fractune (Colours by Barslund)<br />
        c/o Anders Barslund<br />
        Abildgaardsvej 51<br />
        2830 Virum, Denmark<br />
        Tel: (+45) 60 63 40 24<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:legal@fractune.dk">legal@fractune.dk</a>
      </address>

      <h2>2. What Data Do We Collect?</h2>
      <p>When you use Fractune, we collect and process the following types of data:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Image analysis (on-device only):</strong> Photographs of
          facades you analyse are processed entirely on your iPhone and never
          leave the device unless you explicitly choose to contribute the
          analysis to the public dataset.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Anonymous reading metrics (opt-in):</strong> If you accept
          research data sharing, we collect the computed values from each
          analysis: Architectural Fluency F, fractal dimension D, the four
          dimension sub-scores, lacunarity, edge-orientation entropy, spectral
          slope, balance, hierarchical scaling, solid/void ratio, curvature
          ratio, value contrast, the chromatic palette and harmony type, plus
          a contributor ID (a randomly generated UUID stored on your device).
          No data can be linked to your personal identity.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Optional location and orientation:</strong> Latitude,
          longitude, camera heading, and pitch, only when you explicitly
          enable location sharing for a reading. You can toggle this per
          reading and revoke it in app settings at any time.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Optional building metadata:</strong> If you enrich a reading
          with a building's name, address, architect, style, or construction
          year, this metadata is published with the reading.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Optional redacted training images:</strong> If you separately
          consent to image donation, a face-redacted JPEG of the facade is
          included with the reading. Faces are detected and blurred on your
          device before upload.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Queries and support:</strong> If you contact us, we process
          your name, contact details, and query to provide assistance.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Legal Basis and Storage Periods</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Anonymous reading metrics: our legitimate interest (GDPR art. 6(1)(f))
          in researching architectural fluency, validating the F formula, and
          improving the analysis pipeline. Data is published as part of an open
          dataset and cannot be used to identify individuals.
        </li>
        <li>
          Location, orientation, building metadata, and redacted images: your
          explicit consent (GDPR art. 6(1)(a)). You can withdraw consent at any
          time in app settings, after which future readings will not include
          these fields.
        </li>
        <li>
          Erasure requests: you may request deletion of all readings linked to
          your contributor ID at any time. We process erasure requests within
          30 days and log the action for accountability (GDPR art. 30).
        </li>
        <li>
          Queries/support: stored for up to 3 months after last contact unless
          required for dispute or legal documentation.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Purpose of Processing</h2>
      <p>We use your data to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Analyse facades on-device and present results to you</li>
        <li>Build and maintain the public Fractune dataset at <a href="https://sites.fractune.dk">sites.fractune.dk</a></li>
        <li>Calibrate and validate the Architectural Fluency F formula against real-world readings</li>
        <li>Support scientific research into fractal geometry, perceptual aesthetics, and architectural composition</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations (accounting, documentation)</li>
        <li>Defend our rights in case of disputes or regulatory investigations</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Aggregated, anonymised dataset readings may be shared with or sold to
        third parties, such as architecture firms, research institutions, or
        urban planning bodies, for research and product development.
        <strong>No data is ever shared that can identify you as an individual.</strong>
      </p>

      <h2>5. Storage, Security &amp; International Transfers</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Anonymous dataset readings are stored in Apple's CloudKit (public database) under our developer container.</li>
        <li>Your local session history (the readings shown on your device's history view) is stored locally on your iPhone and is not synced to any cloud service.</li>
        <li>Support inquiries are stored securely with access limited to authorised personnel.</li>
        <li>Data is not transferred outside the EU/EEA except as required for secure processing by Apple, who complies with GDPR requirements as a data processor.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6. Cookies and Tracking</h2>
      <p>
        Fractune does not use cookies or tracking technologies to collect data
        about your use of the app or website. We do not use analytics for
        advertising or profiling purposes. The website serves a short-lived
        Apple MapKit JS token to render the public sites map; this token does
        not identify you.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Disclosure to Third Parties</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Service providers and IT suppliers who help us deliver our services (Apple for CloudKit and MapKit; hosting providers for the Astro/Vercel website).</li>
        <li>External advisors (e.g. accountants, legal counsel).</li>
        <li>Other third parties with your consent, or in the case of mergers or legal requirements.</li>
        <li>Anonymised reading metrics, including F, D, and dimension sub-scores, are publicly available via <a href="https://sites.fractune.dk">sites.fractune.dk</a>.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>8. App Attest and Device Authentication</h2>
      <p>
        To prevent abuse of our public dataset, the app uses Apple's
        <strong>App Attest</strong> framework to prove that submissions come
        from a legitimate Fractune install on a real Apple device. App Attest
        does not transmit your Apple ID, device serial number, or any
        personally identifiable data, only a cryptographic attestation that
        the submission originates from an authentic copy of the app. See
        <a href="https://developer.apple.com/documentation/devicecheck/establishing_your_app_s_integrity" rel="noopener">Apple's documentation</a>
        for details.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>You have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Request access to or a copy of your data (provide your contributor ID, found in app settings)</li>
        <li>Request correction, erasure, or restriction of your data</li>
        <li>Object to our processing or to data used for research</li>
        <li>Withdraw your consent at any time (for location, image donation, building metadata)</li>
        <li>Complain to the Danish Data Protection Agency at <a href="https://www.datatilsynet.dk" rel="noopener">www.datatilsynet.dk</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise your rights, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:legal@fractune.dk">legal@fractune.dk</a> or by mail/phone (see above).
      </p>

      <h2>10. Children</h2>
      <p>
        Fractune is not directed at children under the age of 13. We do not
        knowingly collect personal data from children. If you believe a child
        has contributed data through Fractune, please contact us so we can
        promptly delete the affected readings.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to this Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this privacy policy as our services evolve or as required
        by law. Significant changes will be communicated via the app or
        website, and the consent flow will request renewed agreement when the
        scope of data collection materially changes. Your continued use after
        changes means you accept the updated policy.
      </p>

      <p class="caption">Fractune – developed by Colours by Barslund</p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <SiteFooter />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page { padding: 4rem 0 6rem; }
  .page-inner { max-width: 700px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2rem; }
  h1 { font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  p, li { line-height: 1.65; color: var(--color-text-secondary); }
  p { font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  ul, ol { margin-left: 1.25rem; padding-left: 0; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  li { font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .caption { color: var(--color-text-secondary); font-size: 0.93rem; margin-top: 3rem; opacity: 0.85; }
  address { font-style: normal; color: var(--color-text); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.65; }
  strong { color: var(--color-text); font-weight: 600; }
</style>
